Comment link for product link ✨ Skincare secrets around the world (Episode 1)

🧼 Moroccan black soap, also known as beldi soap, is a centuries-old beauty staple used in traditional hammams 

🌿 Made from olive pulp and oil, beldi soap deeply cleanses your skin without disrupting its natural barrier. It softens the skin so impurities and dead cells can be lifted away with ease.

🛁 apply it on warm, damp skin and let it sit for a few minute.

🧤 Then, I exfoliate with exfoliating gloves. It gently removes buildup and dullness so you can feel the difference. It boosts circulation, calms the skin, and leaves it glowing, not stripped.✨

I use it once in a week ❤️❤️ I love this because:
✨ Deeply cleanses
✨ Exfoliates gently
✨ Boosts glow & blood circulation
✨ Preps skin for hydration
✨ Rich in vitamin E & antioxidants

Would you try this kind of ritual in your routine? 🙋🏻‍♀️✨

Some beauty tools may look fancy on shelves, but these? These actually make a difference in how my skin looks and feels: Comment link for products link ✨

🧤 Exfoliating Gloves
For smoother, more even-toned skin. I use them gently in the shower and it helps to exfoliate, unclog pores, and prep my skin for products to sink in beautifully.

❄️ Ice Globes
My favorite way to wake up puffy skin. They’re cooling, calming and I love using them after applying a hydrating serum or just on their own. I keep these inside fridge

🪥 Dry Brush
dry brushing before a shower boosts circulation, exfoliates and gives me that healthy skin glow. Bonus: it feels like a mini self-care ritual.

💅 Nail Brush
A tiny tool with a big impact. I use it to gently clean around and under my nails , especially on no-polish days. Keeps things neat and very handy

Comment link for products links: My Retinol Night Routine (2–3x a Week)✨

This is my retinol night routine — the one I reach for twice or thrice a week for well aging🌙

Retinol can be powerful, so it’s all about prep, patience, and balance.

Here’s what I do:
1️⃣ Gentle Cleanser – to remove the day without disrupting my barrier.
2️⃣ Hydrating Toner – optional, but I like that dewy cushion before actives.
3️⃣ Barrier-Friendly Moisturizer – To support the skin barrier and nourish. 
4️⃣ Retinol – applied on dry skin. Just a pea-sized amount: more isn’t better.
5️⃣ Lip mask ✨

I never skip sunscreen the next morning ☀️
And I don’t mix this with exfoliants on the same night🙋🏻‍♀️

☀️ Why You Shouldn’t Use Sunscreen Spray as Your Primary Protection ✨

Spray sunscreens might feel convenient, but they’re not the best choice for your first layer of sun protection and here’s why:

👉 Inconsistent Coverage: Sprays often don’t deliver an even layer. What looks like enough in the air may not actually reach or stay on your skin uniformly.

👉 Not Enough Product: Studies show that most people underapply with sprays even multiple passes don’t guarantee the recommended amount (roughly 2mg/cm² for proper UV protection).

👉 Easily Missed Areas: With spray, it’s easy to miss spots or go too light in key areas like your ears, neck, or shoulders especially in windy environments.

🧴 Instead, use a lotion or cream sunscreen as your primary application. These allow you to apply and blend thoroughly, ensuring full, reliable protection.

💨 Save sprays for touch-ups or reapplication especially over makeup or on-the-go. But for that first layer? Your skin deserves better coverage.

#skincare #sunscreen #sunscreenspray #skincaretips #skincareroutine #spf #sunscreenspray #sunscreenmist

Pink sunscreen✨ comment link for product link 🙋🏻‍♀️

This is TFIT Tone-Up Sun Fluid SPF50+ PA++++ ☀️
I’ve tried tone-up sunscreens before and most of them left my face looking chalky or unnaturally white. But this one? Surprisingly didn’t.

Yes, it does look a bit white at first, but give it 5–10 minutes and it settles into a bright, even-toned finish that actually looks good. It uses hybrid filters for solid UV protection and feels really comfortable on the skin. Plus, it’s water-resistant.

Now, the pink tint works well on my lighter skin, kind of like a subtle tone corrector but I do notice a very slight white cast. For deeper skin tones, that might not blend as seamlessly, so I wouldn’t call this a universal shade.

I personally like this one but if I had to choose, I’d still pick their tinted sunscreen as my #1. It gives me a more natural, even tone that looks beautiful even on camera. This pink one is my runner-up.

Bought it from Tira and the mrp is ₹1400, but they had some good discount coupons too 🫶

Is the viral Huda Beauty Lip Contour worth ₹2200? Here’s my honest take 💬 comment link for the product link✨

The shades are gorgeous and super pigmented, but if you have dry lips, prep is non-negotiable, otherwise, it can look patchy.
It dries fast, doesn’t transfer, but after lunch… it pretty much disappeared from my lips 😅 So yes, reapplication is a must if you’re eating.
At this price point, I don’t think I’ll be buying more shades. If I knew then what I know now… I probably wouldn’t have purchased it.
This is just my experience though 🙋🏻‍♀️would love to hear yours! 💬✨

4 things that changed my skin for better ❤️Comment link for the products link ✨
🪞Before I even turn on the water, I take a minute to dry brush. It’s this simple, underrated step that boosts circulation, gently exfoliates, and gets my skin prepped to actually absorb the products I use after. It’s like waking up my skin before the real pampering starts.

🌿About 30 minutes before showering, I apply this beautiful Ayurvedic oil and wow, the difference it makes. It softens and nourishes my skin so deeply that after I rinse, my skin feels smoother, with long term use brighter, and I swear it just glows. I am using kottakkal ayurveda nalpamaradi tailam here. I also love nalpamaradi from sitaram ayurveda and kerala ayurveda. It does not leave stain behind on my skin but it surely stains the cloths so be careful about iy 

✨While I’m in the shower, I apply a face mask, multitasking at its finest. No extra time needed, just some extra glow while I shampoo or exfoliate. I love how it turns a basic shower into a mini facial moment. I am using my favorite joseon rice mask here. 

🍯Then comes my favorite part: exfoliating with a sugar scrub. It’s so gentle I can use it daily, but it still makes my skin feel like literal velvet. No irritation, no harshness: just soft, healthy-looking skin. I am using Kundal sugat scrub here. 

TBH I fail to follow all the 4 steps everyday but I at least do it 2-3 times in a week❤️❤️
